parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel shakes or jerks
the power steering assist is intermittent
and the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering torque sensor can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel shakes or jerks
the power steering assist is intermittent
and the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump/module can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause accidents or near-misses, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: Brake lights stay on while driving
brake lights do not illuminate when the brake pedal is depressed
brake lights randomly turn on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or loses power
electrical system failures
issues with the ignition
problems with the cruise control
and faulty wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
transmission issues
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can reduce visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights do not work
low beams do not function
and issues with the wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering can cause the vehicle to be difficult to control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Power steering failure
issues with the steering system
and problems with the electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning brake lights can cause confusion for other drivers, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake lights stay on while driving
turn off when applying the brake pedal
or flash on and off randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can reduce visibility, making it difficult for the driver to see the road and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights fail to turn on
dim
or turn off randomly; headlight bulbs need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning cruise control can cause the vehicle to slow down or speed up unexpectedly, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Cruise control disengages or fails to engage; brake lights turn on when cruise control is engaged.
